<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 3:25PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Thunderstorms with gusty winds and lightning will impact
portions of southeastern Madison, southeastern Beaverhead and south
central Gallatin Counties through 400 PM MDT...
At 323 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Island Park Village, or 8 miles southwest of West Yellowstone, moving
northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 45 mph...lightning and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
West Yellowstone, Targhee Pass, Raynolds Pass and Yellowstone
Village.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
